text.section:
Notwithstanding any other provision of this article, if the dealer fails to provide the consumer with any estimated date required by this subtitle or fails to deliver the household good to the consumer within 2 weeks of the latest estimated delivery date properly established under this subtitle, the consumer may:
Cancel the contract and receive a full refund;
Cancel the contract and receive a credit equal to the deposit;
Negotiate with the dealer a new delivery date; or
Modify the contract by selecting other household goods.
